 {"id":"ultrasearch-c00.8.3","content_hash":"c6405bc3ef9e8f74163c88afc15685ac6c0ae974f01ed7f0d2b09b6456331aca","title":"Metrics emission","description":"Expose lightweight metrics (files indexed, index sizes, search latency, worker CPU/mem) via log or optional HTTP endpoint.","status":"in_progress","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"WhiteStone","created_at":"2025-11-20T23:30:13.65234516Z","updated_at":"2025-11-21T02:29:23.038283358Z","source_repo":".","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ultrasearch-c00.8.3","depends_on_id":"ultrasearch-c00.8.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2025-11-20T23:34:14.306111924Z","created_by":"daemon"},{"issue_id":"ultrasearch-c00.8.3","depends_on_id":"ultrasearch-c00.4.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2025-11-20T23:34:18.645526308Z","created_by":"daemon"}],"comments":[{"id":3,"issue_id":"ultrasearch-c00.8.3","author":"ubuntu","text":"Status 2025-11-20: metrics dependent on tracing/logging plumbing and scheduler/index stats. Plan: minimal prometheus-style counters + histograms; optional HTTP endpoint; log-sampled metrics fallback. Waiting on workspace/service skeleton.","created_at":"2025-11-20T23:43:35Z"},{"id":10,"issue_id":"ultrasearch-c00.8.3","author":"ubuntu","text":"Documented metrics section in config reference (enable flag, bind addr, sample intervals, key metrics names). Implementation pending workspace/scheduler plumbing.","created_at":"2025-11-20T23:46:30Z"},{"id":15,"issue_id":"ultrasearch-c00.8.3","author":"ubuntu","text":"Next action: add lightweight metrics collector in service with periodic log summary (no HTTP yet) using tracing; pending to avoid adding new deps before sync with team.","created_at":"2025-11-20T23:50:03Z"},{"id":17,"issue_id":"ultrasearch-c00.8.3","author":"ubuntu","text":"Added service::metrics::spawn_basic_metrics(interval) placeholder; service main now starts Tokio runtime and logs periodic 'metrics tick' at sample_interval_secs. Will replace with real metrics once scheduler/index data is available.","created_at":"2025-11-20T23:52:13Z"},{"id":21,"issue_id":"ultrasearch-c00.8.3","author":"ubuntu","text":"PinkPond has service reservation to add Prometheus metrics stub. I will pause further service edits; existing placeholder metrics ticker can be replaced by their implementation.","created_at":"2025-11-20T23:55:19Z"},{"id":22,"issue_id":"ultrasearch-c00.8.3","author":"ubuntu","text":"Updated CONFIG_REFERENCE metrics section to align with Prometheus stub: documented request_latency_buckets, worker_failure_threshold, and described current counters/histogram exposed by service scrape.","created_at":"2025-11-20T23:56:24Z"},{"id":23,"issue_id":"ultrasearch-c00.8.3","author":"ubuntu","text":"PinkPond's Prometheus stub landed (service::metrics). I will rebase config-\u003einit_metrics once service changes settle; removed further edits during their reservation.","created_at":"2025-11-20T23:57:01Z"},{"id":28,"issue_id":"ultrasearch-c00.8.3","author":"ubuntu","text":"Wired metrics config into service: core-types metrics section now includes buckets + failure threshold; service metrics init now uses config and removes old ticker. Waiting for c00.1.2 edition fix before fmt/check.","created_at":"2025-11-20T23:59:12Z"},{"id":34,"issue_id":"ultrasearch-c00.8.3","author":"ubuntu","text":"Config -\u003e metrics integration done; waiting for fmt/check after c00.1.2. Placeholder ticker removed.","created_at":"2025-11-21T00:01:48Z"},{"id":36,"issue_id":"ultrasearch-c00.8.3","author":"ubuntu","text":"Metrics threshold now enforced via ServiceMetrics::record_worker_failure (returns threshold reached); request recording helper added; metrics snapshot struct added for status wiring; service exports these helpers.","created_at":"2025-11-21T00:42:28Z"},{"id":39,"issue_id":"ultrasearch-c00.8.3","author":"ubuntu","text":"Added tests for worker failure threshold and request latency recording in service::metrics.","created_at":"2025-11-21T00:43:42Z"},{"id":49,"issue_id":"ultrasearch-c00.8.3","author":"ubuntu","text":"Metrics helper tests added; worker failure threshold enforced.","created_at":"2025-11-21T00:46:34Z"},{"id":54,"issue_id":"ultrasearch-c00.8.3","author":"ubuntu","text":"Metrics wiring pending manifest fix; helpers/tests ready.","created_at":"2025-11-21T00:49:25Z"},{"id":61,"issue_id":"ultrasearch-c00.8.3","author":"ubuntu","text":"Service metrics snapshot_with_queue_state covered by test; metrics helper set aligns with PinkPond snapshot fields.","created_at":"2025-11-21T00:57:11Z"},{"id":65,"issue_id":"ultrasearch-c00.8.3","author":"ubuntu","text":"Added snapshot_with_queue_state test; no further metrics changes while PinkPond holds metrics.rs.","created_at":"2025-11-21T01:03:24Z"},{"id":115,"issue_id":"ultrasearch-c00.8.3","author":"ubuntu","text":"WhiteStone: taking this; will wire ServiceMetrics snapshot into IPC status + prep Prometheus scrape hook.","created_at":"2025-11-21T02:29:54Z"},{"id":118,"issue_id":"ultrasearch-c00.8.3","author":"ubuntu","text":"Implemented IPC latency recording + Prometheus helpers; SearchRequest timeout now serialized as ms-stable; status IPC reuses status_snapshot + metrics global. cargo fmt ok; cargo check currently fails in ntfs-watcher tests (FileMeta PartialEq/FileFlags import).","created_at":"2025-11-21T02:34:36Z"},{"id":120,"issue_id":"ultrasearch-c00.8.3","author":"ubuntu","text":"cargo check --all-targets now passes after the ntfs-watcher/core-types equality fixes.","created_at":"2025-11-21T02:37:27Z"},{"id":121,"issue_id":"ultrasearch-c00.8.3","author":"ubuntu","text":"Added /metrics HTTP scrape (tokio TCP, Prometheus text) via spawn_metrics_http; cmd uses cfg.metrics.bind. Kept global scrape helpers; IPC already records latency. cargo check --all-targets now green.","created_at":"2025-11-21T02:57:12Z"}]}
 {"id":"ultrasearch-c00.8.4","content_hash":"91f33b7bf53f9763fed1fd1296961fb7f6268aaa5915c11856a5ffd46f585d2a","title":"Operational status reporting","description":"Provide status responses in IPC (volumes, index stats, scheduler state), log periodic heartbeats, and surface UI indicators.","notes":"Started operational status reporting: defaults now 'initializing'; /metrics HTTP served; workspace green","status":"in_progress","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"WhiteStone","created_at":"2025-11-20T23:30:17.820632364Z","updated_at":"2025-11-21T02:59:58.10819637Z","source_repo":".","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ultrasearch-c00.8.4","depends_on_id":"ultrasearch-c00.6.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2025-11-20T23:34:24.221304571Z","created_by":"daemon"}],"comments":[{"id":4,"issue_id":"ultrasearch-c00.8.4","author":"ubuntu","text":"Status 2025-11-20: IPC/status API requires IPC server and scheduler/index state structs; blocked until c00.2.x and c00.6.x land. When ready, will expose volumes/index stats/scheduler state and add heartbeat log.","created_at":"2025-11-20T23:43:40Z"},{"id":11,"issue_id":"ultrasearch-c00.8.4","author":"ubuntu","text":"Config reference now lists status fields to expose: volumes (last_usn, journal_id, lag), indices (sizes/segments/last commit), scheduler state, metrics snapshot. Will align IPC Status response accordingly once IPC/service code exists.","created_at":"2025-11-20T23:46:33Z"},{"id":25,"issue_id":"ultrasearch-c00.8.4","author":"ubuntu","text":"Status API still pending IPC/scheduler state; blocked on workspace/editions and IPC schema convergence. Will implement once unblocked.","created_at":"2025-11-20T23:57:16Z"},{"id":30,"issue_id":"ultrasearch-c00.8.4","author":"ubuntu","text":"Extended IPC models for status: VolumeStatus now includes last_usn/journal_id; StatusResponse carries last_index_commit_ts and optional MetricsSnapshot (latencies, worker CPU/mem). Added optional timeout to SearchRequest for latency budgeting.","created_at":"2025-11-21T00:00:37Z"},{"id":31,"issue_id":"ultrasearch-c00.8.4","author":"ubuntu","text":"Status IPC models extended (timeout in SearchRequest, last_usn/journal_id in VolumeStatus, last_index_commit_ts + MetricsSnapshot in StatusResponse). Server wiring still pending IPC/server design.","created_at":"2025-11-21T00:00:56Z"},{"id":33,"issue_id":"ultrasearch-c00.8.4","author":"ubuntu","text":"Next steps: add server handling of StatusRequest (populate volume states, metrics snapshot, last_index_commit_ts) once IPC/server plumbing is ready.","created_at":"2025-11-21T00:01:35Z"},{"id":37,"issue_id":"ultrasearch-c00.8.4","author":"ubuntu","text":"Added service::status::make_status_response helper to populate new StatusResponse fields consistently; still needs real data wiring but models are now exercised via builder.","created_at":"2025-11-21T00:42:33Z"},{"id":38,"issue_id":"ultrasearch-c00.8.4","author":"ubuntu","text":"Note: Duration serde in SearchRequest.timeout relies on std serde support (enabled by default); if workspace trims serde default features later, we must enable serde/std feature explicitly.","created_at":"2025-11-21T00:42:50Z"},{"id":40,"issue_id":"ultrasearch-c00.8.4","author":"ubuntu","text":"Added unit tests covering SearchRequest timeout and VolumeStatus extended fields; more wiring pending once server-side available.","created_at":"2025-11-21T00:44:00Z"},{"id":48,"issue_id":"ultrasearch-c00.8.4","author":"ubuntu","text":"IPC tests added for timeout and volume fields; server wiring still pending and will proceed after manifest stabilizes.","created_at":"2025-11-21T00:46:29Z"},{"id":51,"issue_id":"ultrasearch-c00.8.4","author":"ubuntu","text":"Aligned IPC schema with c00.6.1 updates: added metrics snapshot test, timeout/offset defaults in tests, fields queue_depth/active_workers retained. Service metrics snapshot now exposes queue_depth/active_workers placeholders.","created_at":"2025-11-21T00:48:35Z"},{"id":53,"issue_id":"ultrasearch-c00.8.4","author":"ubuntu","text":"Blocked on manifest/edition fixes before wiring StatusRequest handler; IPC schema aligned and tested.","created_at":"2025-11-21T00:49:18Z"},{"id":126,"issue_id":"ultrasearch-c00.8.4","author":"ubuntu","text":"WhiteStone in_progress: set status defaults to 'initializing' and enabled /metrics HTTP endpoint (uses cfg.metrics.bind). Workspace check green after adding tempfile/memmap2 deps to workspace + core-serialization.","created_at":"2025-11-21T03:00:02Z"},{"id":128,"issue_id":"ultrasearch-c00.8.4","author":"ubuntu","text":"Added init_basic_status_provider + global update helpers (volumes/state/metrics/queue/last_commit) so other modules can push status without carrying handle. Status still defaults to initializing; cargo check green.","created_at":"2025-11-21T03:01:44Z"},{"id":129,"issue_id":"ultrasearch-c00.8.4","author":"ubuntu","text":"SchedulerRuntime now updates status + metrics (queue depth, active_workers, state) using new helper exports; service main wires init_basic_status_provider() + spawn_metrics_http(). Workspace check still green.","created_at":"2025-11-21T03:07:39Z"},{"id":137,"issue_id":"ultrasearch-c00.8.4","author":"ubuntu","text":"SchedulerRuntime now pushes queue depth + active workers + state into StatusProvider and metrics (using global snapshot). Added /metrics TCP server already; service main uses init_basic_status_provider() + clap config. Build green.","created_at":"2025-11-21T03:12:51Z"},{"id":139,"issue_id":"ultrasearch-c00.8.4","author":"ubuntu","text":"Hotfix: left disk IO on non-Windows as placeholder (sysinfo 0.30 lacks counters). Windows path will still use PDH when available. Rest of status/metrics wiring unchanged; cargo check green.","created_at":"2025-11-21T03:15:43Z"},{"id":141,"issue_id":"ultrasearch-c00.8.4","author":"ubuntu","text":"StatusResponse now carries served_by host label; service IPC/status wired; fmt/check/clippy clean.","created_at":"2025-11-21T03:22:42Z"},{"id":143,"issue_id":"ultrasearch